- 1.2.0 | Mar 08 2026:
[New] 12 UAT helper functions: assert_json_field, assert_json_array_length
      (JSON validation with dot-notation); assert_csv_row_count,
      assert_csv_header (CSV validation); assert_output_line_count,
      assert_file_perms, assert_process_running/not_running (general
      assertions); uat_wait_for_condition, uat_wait_for_file,
      uat_wait_for_log (polling replacements for hardcoded sleep);
      uat_cleanup_processes (graceful process teardown with SIGKILL fallback)
[New] 32 new self-tests for all UAT helper functions; 194 tests total
[Fix] uat_cleanup_processes test: fix always-true assertion
[Fix] assert_output_line_count: use arithmetic coercion for wc whitespace trim

- 1.1.0 | Mar 07 2026:
[New] UAT helper library (lib/uat-helpers.bash) — shared assertion primitives
      for BATS-based UAT scenarios: uat_setup, uat_capture, assert_valid_json,
      assert_valid_csv, assert_empty_state_message, assert_no_banner_corruption
[New] UAT Makefile targets (uat, uat-verbose) — run tests/uat/ scenarios via
      batsman_run_direct() path passthrough; invisible to 'make test'
[New] 25 new self-tests for UAT helper library — setup, capture, log, JSON/CSV
      validation, empty-state, banner corruption detection; 162 tests total
[New] README: UAT Scenarios section — directory structure, writing scenarios,
      available helpers, tag convention, running UAT

- 1.0.3 | Mar 02 2026:
[New] install-bats.sh: SHA256 checksum verification for all three pinned
      tarballs (bats-core, bats-support, bats-assert) — download integrity
      backstop compensating for disabled TLS verification on legacy OS
[New] README: migration guide with version-specific upgrade notes for
      consumers — covers BATS 1.13.0 run-variable unset breaking change,
      SHA256 checksum verification, parallelism reduction, CLI strictness
[New] 60 new self-tests — CLI argument parsing (20), build/clean/routing
      (19), execution modes (12), install-bats.sh (7), _batsman_done
      flag (2); 133 tests total
[Change] Demote default parallelism from nproc*2 to nproc for both
      intra-OS and cross-OS parallelism — prevents compounding container
      storms on test-all-parallel targets
[Fix] Harden CLI argument parsing — shift guards on value-consuming flags,
      batsman_run() propagates parse/build failures, --timeout numeric
      validation, unknown --flags warn instead of silently routing to
      direct mode, end-of-options (--) support
[Fix] install-bats.sh: harden download pipeline — file-based download
      replacing stdout pipe (prevents corruption on fallback retry),
      set -o pipefail, network timeouts (wget --timeout=60, curl
      --connect-timeout 30 --max-time 120)
[Fix] --help and --version now return instead of exit in sourced library —
      prevents process termination when called from sourced context; adds
      _batsman_done flag checked by batsman_run() for clean short-circuit
[Fix] Add nproc fallback chain (nproc || sysctl -n hw.logicalcpu || echo 1)
      in run-tests-core.sh and Makefile.tests — enables macOS host support
      where GNU nproc is unavailable
[Fix] self-test.yml: widen push branch pattern from '1.*' to '[0-9]*.*' —
      CI triggers on any version branch, not just 1.x
[Fix] Makefile.tests parallel xargs targets: wrap commands with sh -c to
      emit per-OS failure banners to stderr — xargs -P exit 123 no longer
      hides which OS targets failed
[Fix] Makefile.tests clean-all regex: add hyphen to character class so
      hyphenated project names (e.g., my-project) are matched for image
      cleanup
[Fix] Documentation accuracy pass — correct help text, README, and
      CHANGELOG for parallelism, TLS fallback, container naming, and
      formatter behavior

- 1.0.2 | Feb 28 2026:
[Change] BATS version bump 1.11.0 → 1.13.0 — unlocks --abort (fail-fast),
      --negative-filter, BATS_TEST_TIMEOUT bug fixes, JUnit XML fixes;
      BATS Bash floor remains 3.2+ (batsman requires 4.1+/CentOS 6)
[New] --version CLI option and BATSMAN_VERSION variable — consumer projects
      and CI can query the batsman version programmatically
[New] --timeout SECS CLI option and BATSMAN_TEST_TIMEOUT env var for per-test
      timeout protection (passed as BATS_TEST_TIMEOUT into containers)
[New] --abort CLI option for fail-fast — stops on first test failure; in
      parallel mode applies per-group (each container aborts independently)
[New] --filter-tags TAG CLI option for tag-based test selection — passthrough
      to bats --filter-tags (comma-separated, ! to negate; requires BATS 1.8.0+)
[New] --report-dir DIR CLI option, BATSMAN_REPORT_DIR env var, and Makefile
      test-report target for JUnit XML report generation; sequential/direct
      produce DIR/report.xml, parallel produces DIR/group-N/report.xml per
      group; CI workflow uploads artifacts (14-day retention) and writes job
      summary with test/failure/error/skipped/duration table
[New] --clean CLI option and batsman_clean() function for Docker image cleanup
      — removes base and test images after test run (test exit codes preserved);
      three modes: current OS (default), --all (all project images),
      --dangling-only; automatic dangling prune after every build; Makefile
      targets: clean, clean-all, clean-dangling
[New] CI concurrency groups — rapid pushes to the same branch auto-cancel
      superseded runs per-OS; optional concurrency-group input for custom prefix
[New] CI workflow: test-path input (default /opt/tests) and reports boolean
      input (default true) for per-caller customization
[Fix] Makefile clean-all: match variant image suffixes (e.g., yara-x) in
      addition to standard OS targets
[Fix] CI workflow: JUnit summary step tolerates missing XML attributes
      (errors, skipped) — grep failures no longer kill the step under set -e
[New] Self-test suite — batsman tests itself via self-bootstrap; unit tests
      cover argument parsing, variable validation, variant mapping, parallel
      distribution, and file discovery (74 tests across 4 test files)
[New] CI workflow for self-tests — standalone workflow (cannot reuse test.yml
      because infra IS the repo root, not a submodule); lint + Docker build +
      BATS run with JUnit reports and job summary

- 1.0.1 | Feb 27 2026:
[Fix] dockerfiles: Rocky 10 base image name rockylinux:10 → rockylinux/rockylinux:10
      (not published to Docker Hub library, only to rockylinux org namespace)
[New] BATSMAN_BASE_OS_MAP: variant-to-base OS mapping for project-specific
      non-OS targets (e.g., yara-x → debian12 base)
[New] include/Makefile.tests — parameterized GNU Make include with per-OS,
      tier-grouped, and cross-OS parallel targets via $(eval $(call))
[New] .github/workflows/test.yml — reusable CI workflow with two-phase
      Docker build, GHA cache for base images, workflow_call interface
[Fix] dockerfiles: Rocky 8/9 coreutils-single conflict with coreutils
      on minimal images — omit coreutils from package list

